examples.en: They acquired a new pet.

He acquired a strong liking for sports.
I acquired a passing knowledge of Chinese.
The normal way in which nationality is acquired is through birth.

James Dean acquired the status of a cult hero.
That kind of knowledge is acquired, not inborn.
In her last job she acquired a reputation as a troublemaker.
I acquired a strong aversion to television.
Elsie acquired a good knowledge of Chinese.
He is studying the way that language is acquired by children.
...having just acquired his driver's license that morning, the teen agreed with alacrity to drive his cousin to the airport...
She had acquired a taste for European beer.
The company was acquired at a high valuation.
He acquired kudos just by appearing on television.
The ball seemed to have acquired a life of its own.

These were estates his father questionably acquired.

Gradually, I acquired a rudimentary knowledge of music.
The actor James Dean acquired the status of a cult hero.
